Section Summary: A teacher should make a good impression, both personally and professionally, when applying for a position. To be successful, a teacher needs a good general education, as well as specialized knowledge in their chosen field, and should continually seek to broaden their education. Carelessness in filling out application forms and failing to choose responsible references can harm a teacher's chances of being hired. A teacher's motivation for applying for a position should be based on a desire to improve professionally, rather than just seeking higher pay. Ultimately, a teacher's goal should be to continually improve and specialize in their field, as seen in the example of the young woman who took a year to further her training.
